===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|weder|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*wedrą}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*wedʰrom}} (={{m|ine-pro|*we-dʰrom}}). Cognate with West Frisian {{term|waar|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|weer|lang=nl}}, Low German {{term|Weder|lang=nds}}, German {{term|Wetter|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|vejr|lang=da}}, Swedish {{term|väder|lang=sv}}; also more distantly related to Russian {{term|вёдро||fair weather|tr=vyodro|lang=ru}} and perhaps Albanian {{term|vrëndë||light rain|lang=sq}}.

